kind.prompt:
Build a complete offline-first Blazor WebAssembly PWA for building inspectors on construction sites. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-41082ee95512431f9ffffa6325d0f985/SiteInspector/`.

## Project Structure
- **SiteInspector/** (server project) - hosts app, API endpoints for sync
- **SiteInspector.Client/** (WebAssembly) - all UI components, runs in browser

## Architecture Decisions
- **Offline-first**: All data stored in IndexedDB via JS interop. App works fully without network.
- **PWA**: Service worker caches all assets for offline use. Add manifest.json.
- **Sync**: When online, pending data syncs to server API endpoints.
- **Mobile-first**: Touch-friendly UI, large tap targets, responsive layout.
- **No auth** in this version.

## What to Build

### 1. Models (in .Client project, create `Models/` folder)

```csharp
// Models/InspectionModels.cs
namespace SiteInspector.Client.Models;

public class ConstructionSite
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Address { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
}

public class Inspection
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string SiteId { get; set; } = "";
    public string SiteName { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime InspectionDate { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
    public List<ChecklistItem> ChecklistItems { get; set; } = new();
    public List<PhotoRecord> Photos { get; set; } = new();
    public InspectionStatus Status { get; set; } = InspectionStatus.InProgress;
    public bool IsSynced { get; set; } = false;
}

public class ChecklistItem
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string Category { get; set; } = "";
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public CheckResult Result { get; set; } = CheckResult.NotChecked;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
}

public class PhotoRecord
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string FileName { get; set; } = "";
    public string ContentType { get; set; } = "image/jpeg";
    public string Base64Data { get; set; } = "";
    public string Caption { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime TakenAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
}

public enum CheckResult { NotChecked, Pass, Fail, NotApplicable }
public enum InspectionStatus { InProgress, Completed }
```

### 2. IndexedDB JavaScript Module (in .Client/wwwroot/js/indexedDb.js)

Create a JS module that provides IndexedDB CRUD operations:
- `openDb()` - opens/creates the database with object stores: `sites`, `inspections`
- `getAll(storeName)` - get all records from a store
- `getById(storeName, id)` - get single record
- `put(storeName, record)` - add or update a record
- `delete(storeName, id)` - delete a record
- `getByIndex(storeName, indexName, value)` - query by index

Database name: "SiteInspectorDb", version 1.
Stores: 
- "sites" with keyPath "id"
- "inspections" with keyPath "id", index on "siteId" and "isSynced"

### 3. Storage Service (in .Client/Services/)

```csharp
// Services/ILocalStorageService.cs
namespace SiteInspector.Client.Services;

public interface ILocalStorageService
{
    Task InitializeAsync();
    Task<List<ConstructionSite>> GetSitesAsync();
    Task<ConstructionSite?> GetSiteAsync(string id);
    Task SaveSiteAsync(ConstructionSite site);
    Task DeleteSiteAsync(string id);
    Task<List<Inspection>> GetInspectionsAsync();
    Task<List<Inspection>> GetInspectionsBySiteAsync(string siteId);
    Task<Inspection?> GetInspectionAsync(string id);
    Task SaveInspectionAsync(Inspection inspection);
    Task DeleteInspectionAsync(string id);
    Task<List<Inspection>> GetUnsyncedInspectionsAsync();
    Task MarkAsSyncedAsync(string inspectionId);
}
```

Implement `LocalStorageService` using IJSRuntime to call the IndexedDB module. Use `IJSRuntime.InvokeAsync` to call JS functions.

### 4. Sync Service (in .Client/Services/)

```csharp
// Services/SyncService.cs
namespace SiteInspector.Client.Services;

public interface ISyncService
{
    event Action<SyncStatus>? OnStatusChanged;
    SyncStatus CurrentStatus { get; }
    int PendingCount { get; }
    Task SyncAsync();
}

public enum SyncStatus { Idle, Syncing, Success, Failed, Offline }
```

Implement SyncService that:
- Uses HttpClient to POST unsynced inspections to `/api/inspections/sync`
- Checks navigator.onLine via JS interop
- After successful sync, marks inspections as synced
- Provides status updates via event

### 5. Connectivity Service (in .Client/Services/)

A service that monitors online/offline status using JS interop (window online/offline events) and triggers sync when coming back online.

### 6. Pages (in .Client/Pages/)

**Remove the default template pages** (Counter.razor, Weather.razor, Home.razor). Create:

#### Home.razor (`@page "/"`)
- Shows list of construction sites
- "Add Site" button
- Each site shows name, address, count of inspections
- Tap a site to see its inspections
- Sync status indicator at top

#### SiteDetail.razor (`@page "/site/{SiteId}"`)
- Shows site details
- List of inspections for this site (sorted by date, newest first)
- "New Inspection" button
- Each inspection shows date, status (in-progress/completed), sync status icon

#### InspectionPage.razor (`@page "/inspection/{InspectionId}"`)
- Shows the active inspection
- Tab-like sections: Checklist | Photos | Notes
- Checklist section: list of items, each with tap-to-toggle Pass/Fail/NA buttons
- Photos section: camera capture button, list of attached photos with captions
- Notes section: textarea for general notes
- "Complete Inspection" button
- Auto-saves on every change

#### NewSite.razor (`@page "/site/new"`)
- Simple form: Name, Address
- Save button

#### NewInspection.razor (`@page "/site/{SiteId}/new-inspection"`)
- Creates a new inspection with a default safety checklist
- Immediately navigates to InspectionPage

### 7. Default Safety Checklist Template

Create a static helper that returns a default checklist:
```
Category: Fall Protection
- Guardrails in place and secure
- Safety nets installed where required
- Personal fall arrest systems available

Category: Scaffolding
- Scaffolding properly erected and braced
- Planking in good condition
- Access ladders in place

Category: Electrical
- GFCI protection in use
- Electrical cords in good condition
- Temporary wiring properly installed

Category: Housekeeping
- Work areas clean and orderly
- Debris properly disposed
- Walkways clear of obstructions

Category: PPE
- Hard hats worn in designated areas
- Safety glasses/goggles available
- High-visibility vests worn
```

### 8. Layout and Styling

Replace the default MainLayout with a mobile-first layout:
- Bottom navigation bar (Sites | Sync)
- Top header with app name
- No sidebar (mobile-first)
- Large touch targets (min 44px)
- Status bar showing online/offline and pending sync count

Create `app.css` in .Client/wwwroot with mobile-first styles. Use CSS variables for theming. Make checklist items large and easy to tap. Use green/red/gray for Pass/Fail/NotChecked.

### 9. PWA Support

In the SERVER project's `wwwroot/`:
- Create `manifest.json` with app name "Site Inspector", theme color, icons
- Create `service-worker.js` that caches all static assets and the blazor framework files using a cache-first strategy
- Create a simple `icon-192.png` and `icon-512.png` placeholder (just create the manifest referencing them, noting they need real icons)

In `App.razor`, add:
- `<link rel="manifest" href="manifest.json" />`
- `<meta name="theme-color" content="#1a5276" />`
- Service worker registration script

### 10. Server API Endpoints

In the server `Program.cs`, add minimal API endpoints:
- `POST /api/inspections/sync` - accepts a list of inspections, stores them (use in-memory list for now), returns success
- `GET /api/inspections` - returns all synced inspections
- `POST /api/sites/sync` - accepts sites

### 11. Client Program.cs

Register all services:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<ILocalStorageService, LocalStorageService>();
builder.Services.AddScoped<ISyncService, SyncService>();
builder.Services.AddScoped<ConnectivityService>();
builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
```

### 12. Photo Capture

For photo capture, create a JS module `.Client/wwwroot/js/camera.js` that:
- Opens a file input with `accept="image/*" capture="environment"` (uses device camera on mobile)
- Reads the selected file as base64
- Returns the base64 data and filename

Use this from a `PhotoCapture.razor` component.

## Important Implementation Notes

- All interactive components go in `.Client` project
- Use `System.Text.Json` for serialization in IndexedDB (serialize C# objects to JSON strings for storage)
- The app must be fully functional with NO network — all CRUD operations work against IndexedDB
- Sync is "nice to have" — the app never blocks on network
- Keep the UI simple and fast — minimize re-renders, use large buttons
- Don't use any NuGet packages beyond what's already there — use raw JS interop for IndexedDB
- Remove the Counter.razor and Weather.razor default pages
- After building everything, run `dotnet build` on the solution to verify it compiles

## File locations summary:
- Server project: `/tmp/sv-41082ee95512431f9ffffa6325d0f985/SiteInspector/SiteInspector/`
- Client project: `/tmp/sv-41082ee95512431f9ffffa6325d0f985/SiteInspector/SiteInspector.Client/`
- Solution: `/tmp/sv-41082ee95512431f9ffffa6325d0f985/SiteInspector/SiteInspector.sln`

